  "doc_id": "15427",
  "text": "Investigators can use a very well known multiagent architecture known as BDI, which specifies the internal structure of an agent through three concepts: Belief, Desire and Intention [CITATION_1] ]. An agents belief is its perception of the surrounding environment. Desire is the agents motivational states or goals, and an agents intention is its current decision in order to reach his goals (desires). Agent intentions are realized through intelligent planning [CITATION_2] ]. Following the previous example, an electricity generator can forecast power market's future, and plan not to forward sale its electricity supplies because of a rise in electricity prices in the near future. As this example portrays, the sort of planning problems in a multiagent system that simulates an infrastructure system is usually complicated and have to be discovered and optimized in a multidimensional space and hence requires complex techniques.",
